name: Rubicon Programs - Career Advancement Center
description: Provides job training, placement services, and career counseling for Oakland residents. Specializes in helping individuals with barriers to employment, including criminal records.
eligibility_criteria: Open to all Oakland residents, specializes in serving individuals with criminal records

name: Oakland Private Industry Council (PIC)
description: Workforce development organization offering job training, placement services, and support for youth and adults in Oakland.
eligibility_criteria: Oakland residents seeking employment services

name: Cypress Mandela Training Center
description: Pre-apprenticeship construction training program for Oakland residents. Provides hands-on skills training and job placement in the building trades.
eligibility_criteria: Oakland residents interested in construction careers, particularly those facing barriers to employment

name: The Homecoming Project
description: Comprehensive reentry services including employment support, case management, and community connection for formerly incarcerated individuals.
eligibility_criteria: Formerly incarcerated individuals returning to Oakland

name: Building Opportunities for Self-Sufficiency (BOSS)
description: Provides employment services, housing assistance, and support for homeless and low-income individuals in Oakland.
eligibility_criteria: Low-income and homeless individuals in Oakland

name: Building Hope Transitional Housing
description: Transitional housing program for formerly incarcerated men providing safe, supportive housing while they rebuild their lives.
eligibility_criteria: Men recently released from incarceration, must be referred by parole or probation

name: East Bay Housing Organizations (EBHO)
description: Provides housing counseling, rental assistance information, and resources for finding affordable housing in Oakland.
eligibility_criteria: Low to moderate income Oakland residents seeking housing assistance

name: LifeLong Medical Care - Fruitvale Community Clinic
description: Homeless outreach and housing navigation services as part of comprehensive community health center.
eligibility_criteria: Uninsured or underinsured Oakland residents, homeless individuals prioritized

name: Oakland Housing Authority - Supportive Housing
description: Provides supportive housing and Section 8 voucher information for low-income Oakland residents.
eligibility_criteria: Very low income Oakland residents, priority for homeless and disabled individuals

name: St. Mary's Center
description: Comprehensive services for homeless and low-income seniors and adults, including housing assistance, meals, and case management.
eligibility_criteria: Low-income adults 55+ in Oakland

name: Alameda County Community Food Bank
description: Large food bank serving Alameda County with Oakland distribution sites. Provides groceries and fresh produce to families in need.
hours: Mon-Fri 9am-5pm, Distribution times vary by site
eligibility_criteria: Low-income individuals and families in Alameda County

name: St. Vincent de Paul - Oakland Dining Room
description: Free hot meals served daily, no questions asked. One of Oakland's longest-running meal programs serving the homeless and low-income community.
eligibility_criteria: Open to all, no requirements

name: Lakeview Pantry at Lake Merritt United Methodist Church
description: Community food pantry providing groceries to Oakland families. Open to all regardless of faith or background.
eligibility_criteria: Oakland residents in need, proof of Oakland residency required

name: Oakland Unified School District - Community Meals
description: Free meals for children and families at various Oakland school sites. Summer meal program and after-school nutrition.
hours: School year: Mon-Fri 7:30am-8:30am, 11am-1pm. Summer: varies by site
eligibility_criteria: All children 18 and under, no income requirements
accessibility: Wheelchair accessible at all school sites

name: LifeLong Medical Care - Multiple Clinics
description: Network of community health clinics providing comprehensive primary care to uninsured and underinsured Oakland residents.
eligibility_criteria: All Oakland residents, sliding fee scale based on income, no one turned away
accessibility: Wheelchair accessible, multiple locations throughout Oakland

name: Tiburcio Vasquez Health Center
description: Federally Qualified Health Center providing comprehensive medical, dental, and behavioral health services to the Latino community and all Oakland residents.
eligibility_criteria: All Oakland residents regardless of immigration status or ability to pay

name: Alameda Health Consortium - West Oakland Health Center
description: Community health center serving West Oakland with primary care, pediatrics, and specialty services.
eligibility_criteria: West Oakland residents, sliding fee scale available

name: La Familia Counseling Service
description: Culturally responsive mental health and substance abuse treatment services for Latino families and individuals in Oakland.
eligibility_criteria: Oakland residents, sliding fee scale, Medi-Cal accepted

name: Bonita House - Mental Health & Wellness Center
description: Community mental health center providing counseling, psychiatric services, and peer support for Oakland residents.
eligibility_criteria: Oakland residents experiencing mental health challenges, sliding fee scale

name: Bay Area Community Services (BACS)
description: Mental health services and supportive housing for individuals with serious mental illness and co-occurring disorders.
eligibility_criteria: Adults with serious mental illness, Medi-Cal accepted

name: HealthRIGHT 360 - Oakland Center
description: Comprehensive substance abuse treatment including residential, outpatient, and medication-assisted treatment programs.
eligibility_criteria: Individuals struggling with substance abuse, sliding fee scale, Medi-Cal accepted

name: Options Recovery Services
description: Outpatient substance abuse treatment with a focus on trauma-informed care and recovery support.
eligibility_criteria: Adults seeking substance abuse treatment, sliding fee scale

name: MedMark Treatment Centers Oakland
description: Medication-assisted treatment (MAT) clinic specializing in methadone and buprenorphine treatment for opioid addiction.
eligibility_criteria: Adults with opioid use disorder, self-pay and Medi-Cal accepted

name: East Bay Community Law Center
description: Free legal services for low-income Oakland residents, including criminal record clearing, housing defense, and public benefits advocacy.
hours: Mon-Fri 9am-5pm, walk-in hours vary by clinic
eligibility_criteria: Low-income Oakland residents, income guidelines apply

name: Bay Area Legal Aid - Oakland Office
description: Free civil legal services for low-income individuals and families in Alameda County. Handles housing, public benefits, and consumer issues.
eligibility_criteria: Low-income individuals and families, 125% of federal poverty level

name: Legal Services for Prisoners with Children (LSPC)
description: Legal advocacy organization fighting for the rights of incarcerated parents, children, and families. Provides know-your-rights education and policy advocacy.
eligibility_criteria: Incarcerated parents, formerly incarcerated individuals, families affected by incarceration

name: AC Transit - Clipper START Program
description: Discounted transit passes for low-income riders on AC Transit buses throughout Oakland and the East Bay.
eligibility_criteria: Income at or below 200% of federal poverty level

name: Cycles of Change
description: Bicycle education and distribution program providing free bikes and safety training to Oakland youth and adults.
eligibility_criteria: Oakland residents, priority for low-income individuals and families

name: Alameda County Social Services - CalFresh & General Assistance
description: County social services providing benefits enrollment and assistance obtaining identification documents.
eligibility_criteria: Alameda County residents, varies by program

name: DMV Field Office - Oakland Claremont
description: California Department of Motor Vehicles office providing ID cards, driver's licenses, and vehicle registration.
hours: Mon, Tue, Thu, Fri 8am-5pm, Wed 9am-5pm, closed weekends
eligibility_criteria: California residents, proof of identity and residency required

name: Laney College
description: Community college offering degree programs, vocational training, and adult education including GED preparation.
eligibility_criteria: California residents, free for low-income students via Board of Governors Fee Waiver

name: Oakland Adult & Career Education (OACE)
description: Adult education programs including high school diploma, GED, ESL, and career technical education.
eligibility_criteria: Adults 18+ seeking education, free for Oakland residents

name: Merritt College
description: Community college in the Oakland hills offering degree and certificate programs with strong health sciences and environmental programs.
eligibility_criteria: California residents, free for low-income students via fee waivers
accessibility: Wheelchair accessible, shuttle service from parking

name: Oakland Community Clothes Closet
description: Free clothing closet providing professional attire for job interviews and everyday clothing for families in need.
eligibility_criteria: Oakland residents in need, referral letter helpful but not required

name: Dress for Success East Bay
description: Provides professional attire, career development tools, and network of support for women entering the workforce.
eligibility_criteria: Women actively job searching or recently employed, referral from partner organization required

name: Allen Temple Baptist Church - Community Outreach
description: Historic Oakland church with extensive community programs including food pantry, job readiness, and family support services.
eligibility_criteria: Open to all Oakland residents regardless of faith, some programs have specific criteria

name: Acts Full Gospel Church - New Beginnings Program
description: Faith-based residential recovery program for men struggling with addiction and homelessness.
eligibility_criteria: Men struggling with addiction and/or homelessness, must complete intake interview

name: Coalition for Safe Oakland Communities (CSOC)
description: Community-based organization providing wraparound services for Oakland residents affected by violence and incarceration.
eligibility_criteria: Oakland residents affected by violence or incarceration

name: Oakland Public Library - Main Branch
description: Public library providing free computer access, internet, resume help, and community resources.
eligibility_criteria: Free library card for all Oakland residents

name: Safe Passages - Family Resource Centers
description: Family resource centers throughout Oakland providing parent education, child development services, and family support.
address: Multiple locations - main office 1539 Fruitvale Ave
eligibility_criteria: Families with children 0-18 in Oakland

name: Alameda County Office of Education - Community Schools
description: Coordinates community schools initiative providing wraparound services at school sites including health, social services, and family engagement.
eligibility_criteria: Students and families in Oakland and Alameda County public schools

name: Oakland Workforce Development Board
description: Coordinates Oakland's workforce system connecting job seekers with training and employment opportunities.
eligibility_criteria: Oakland job seekers, priority for individuals facing barriers to employment
